The article discusses a preview of Vice President Harris' visit to the Bahamas. It is described as a historic visit, as she will be the highest-ranking U.S. official to visit the Bahamas since its independence in 1973. The Vice President will have a bilateral meeting with Prime Minister Davis and co-host the U.S.-Caribbean Leaders Meeting. The meeting will focus on addressing the climate crisis through the U.S.-Caribbean Partnership to Address the Climate Crisis 2030 (PACC 2030). The Vice President will also discuss issues such as firearms trafficking, the humanitarian and security crisis in Haiti, and the establishment of new embassies and diplomatic support in the Eastern Caribbean. The article mentions that the Vice President has been actively engaged with Caribbean leaders to strengthen the U.S.-Caribbean relationship.